              }
            }
          ],
          "fingerprints": {
            "clementine/v1": "WSTG-INPV-04:http://ec2-18-188-101-84.us-east-2.compute.amazonaws.com/vulnerabilities/fi/"
          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "1. **Whitelist approach**: Replace free-form file inclusion with a whitelist of allowed page names. Map user-supplied values to filenames using a lookup table \u2014 never pass user input directly to include/require.\n2. **Input sanitization**: Strip `../`, `..%2F`, `..%252F`, and null bytes from the `page` parameter before use.\n3. **PHP configuration**: Set `open_basedir` in php.ini to restrict file access to the web root directory. Disable `allow_url_include` and `allow_url_fopen` to prevent RFI.\n4. **Principle of least privilege**: Run the web server as a low-privilege user (`www-data`) with no read access to sensitive files like `/etc/shadow`, `/proc/self/environ`, or private keys.\n5. **WAF/IDS**: Deploy a WAF rule to block path traversal sequences in query parameters."
              }
            }
          ]
