          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "The server discloses its exact version in the Server response header on every HTTP response: \"Apache/2.4.25 (Debian)\". Apache 2.4.25 was released in December 2016 and has numerous known CVEs. Open ports per nmap: TCP/22 (SSH - OpenSSH 8.7), TCP/80 (HTTP - Apache 2.4.25). Ports 443, 3306, 8080, 8443, 21 are filtered. The SSH service (OpenSSH 8.7) is also accessible, representing an additional attack surface if weak credentials are in use. No reverse proxy or CDN headers detected (no Via, CF-RAY, X-Cache, etc.)."
          },
          "locations": [
