        {
          "ruleId": "IAM_CHECK_SAML_PROVIDERS_STS",
          "level": "note",
          "message": {
            "text": "**IAM SAML providers** enable **federated role assumption** via STS `AssumeRoleWithSAML`.\n\nThis evaluates whether such providers exist in the account."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "arn:aws:iam::760689105616:root"
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fingerprints": {
            "clementine/v1": "iam_check_saml_providers_sts:arn:aws:iam::760689105616:root"
          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "Adopt **SAML federation** to issue **short-lived STS credentials**. Map users to roles with **least privilege**, enforce **MFA** at the IdP, and set conservative session durations. Retire IAM user access keys for interactive use and monitor role sessions as **defense in depth**. *If federation isn't possible*, tightly scope, rotate, and audit keys."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "IAM_SUPPORT_ROLE_CREATED",
          "level": "note",
          "message": {
            "text": "Presence of an **IAM role** that has the AWS managed `AWSSupportAccess` policy attached, designating a support role for interacting with **AWS Support Center** and related tooling."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AWSSupportAccess"
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fingerprints": {
            "clementine/v1": "iam_support_role_created:arn:aws:iam::aws:policy/AWSSupportAccess"
          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "Create a dedicated IAM role for AWS Support with `AWSSupportAccess` and:\n- Restrict who can assume it; require MFA and time-bound access\n- Enforce **least privilege** and **separation of duties**\n- Monitor usage via audit logs and review assignments regularly"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CLOUDWATCH_CHANGES_TO_NETWORK_ACLS_ALARM_CONFIGURED",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "CloudTrail records for **Network ACL changes** are matched by a CloudWatch Logs metric filter with an associated alarm for events like `CreateNetworkAcl`, `CreateNetworkAclEntry`, `DeleteNetworkAcl`, `DeleteNetworkAclEntry`, `ReplaceNetworkAclEntry`, and `ReplaceNetworkAclAssociation`."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "arn:aws:logs:us-east-2:760689105616:log-group"
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fingerprints": {
            "clementine/v1": "cloudwatch_changes_to_network_acls_alarm_configured:arn:aws:logs:us-east-2:760689105616:log-group"
          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "Implement a CloudWatch Logs metric filter and alarm for NACL change events from CloudTrail and route alerts to responders. Enforce **least privilege** on NACL management, require **change control**, and use **defense in depth** with configuration monitoring and flow logs to validate and monitor network posture."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CLOUDWATCH_CHANGES_TO_NETWORK_GATEWAYS_ALARM_CONFIGURED",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "CloudWatch log metric filters and alarms for **network gateway changes** are identified by matching CloudTrail events such as `CreateCustomerGateway`, `DeleteCustomerGateway`, `AttachInternetGateway`, `CreateInternetGateway`, `DeleteInternetGateway`, and `DetachInternetGateway` in log groups that receive trail logs."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "arn:aws:logs:us-east-2:760689105616:log-group"
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fingerprints": {
            "clementine/v1": "cloudwatch_changes_to_network_gateways_alarm_configured:arn:aws:logs:us-east-2:760689105616:log-group"
          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "Send CloudTrail to CloudWatch Logs and create a metric filter for the listed gateway events with an alarm that notifies responders. Enforce **least privilege** for gateway modifications, require change approvals, and route alerts to monitored channels as part of **defense in depth**."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CLOUDWATCH_CHANGES_TO_NETWORK_ROUTE_TABLES_ALARM_CONFIGURED",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "**VPC route table changes** are captured from **CloudTrail logs** by a **CloudWatch Logs metric filter** with an associated **alarm** for events like `CreateRoute`, `CreateRouteTable`, `ReplaceRoute`, `ReplaceRouteTableAssociation`, `DeleteRoute`, `DeleteRouteTable`, and `DisassociateRouteTable`."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "arn:aws:logs:us-east-2:760689105616:log-group"
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fingerprints": {
            "clementine/v1": "cloudwatch_changes_to_network_route_tables_alarm_configured:arn:aws:logs:us-east-2:760689105616:log-group"
          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "Implement a **CloudWatch Logs metric filter and alarm** on CloudTrail for these route table events and notify responders. Enforce **least privilege** for route modifications, require **change control**, and apply **defense in depth** with VPC Flow Logs and guardrails to prevent and quickly contain unsafe routing changes."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CLOUDWATCH_CHANGES_TO_VPCS_ALARM_CONFIGURED",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "**CloudTrail events** for **VPC configuration changes** are captured in CloudWatch Logs with a metric filter and an associated alarm. The filter targets actions like `CreateVpc`, `DeleteVpc`, `ModifyVpcAttribute`, and VPC peering operations to surface when network topology is altered."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "arn:aws:logs:us-east-2:760689105616:log-group"
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fingerprints": {
            "clementine/v1": "cloudwatch_changes_to_vpcs_alarm_configured:arn:aws:logs:us-east-2:760689105616:log-group"
          },
          "fixes": [
            {
              "description": {
                "text": "Create a CloudWatch Logs metric filter and alarm on CloudTrail for critical **VPC change events**, and notify responders. Apply **least privilege** to network changes, require change approvals, and use **defense in depth** (segmentation, route controls) to prevent and contain unauthorized modifications."
              }
            }
          ]
        },
